%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Overwhelming%20evidence%20Venezuela%20opposition%20won%20election%20-%20Blinken%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722563488000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Fa863%2Flive%2F02fd75f0-506c-11ef-9e94-9b37c98c6c42.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd1d10453zno%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20secretary%20of%20state%20insists%20Venezuelans'%20votes%20in%20the%20recent%20presidential%20election%20%26quot%3Bmust%20count%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A127%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd1d10453zno%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd1d10453zno.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd1d10453zno.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222%20renowned%20strategists%20say%20the%20US%20should%20defend%20Taiwan%20with%20nuclear%20strikes.%20Experts%20say%20such%20talk%20is%20just%20a%20taste%20of%20what's%20to%20come.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20missile%20system%20on%20the%20background%20of%20a%20sunset%20sky.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a9fdbf1a227600e633001c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20say%20there's%20a%20shift%20among%20leading%20minds%20in%20the%20US%20to%20a%20more%20aggressive%20nuclear%20posture%20against%20China.%3Cp%3EAnton%20Petrus%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETwo%20Atlantic%20Council%20papers%20on%20a%20Taiwan%20war%20suggested%20the%20US%20plan%20for%20nuclear%20strikes%20on%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20were%20met%20with%20backlash%20from%20some%20nuclear%20scholars%2C%20who%20worry%20such%20rhetoric%20only%20provokes%20Beijing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20debate%20underscores%20a%20shift%20among%20leading%20thinkers%20toward%20a%20more%20aggressive%20nuclear%20posture.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESipping%20coffee%20on%20a%20winter%20break%20morning%2C%20David%20Kearn%20of%20St.%20John's%20University%20scanned%20through%20his%20day's%20list%20of%20memos%20and%20reports%20when%20a%20new%20paper%20caught%20his%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20role%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20a%20Taiwan%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20its%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublished%20by%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20in%20late%20November%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fin-depth-research-reports%2Fissue-brief%2Fthe-role-of-nuclear-weapons-in-a-taiwan-crisis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20report%20%3C%2Fa%3Ediscussed%20how%20a%20potential%20US-China%20war%20over%20Taiwan%20might%20play%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20the%20Pentagon%20might%20win%20with%20tactical%20nuclear%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKearn%20was%20stunned.%20This%20was%20coming%20from%20a%20serious%20analyst%20for%20an%20organization%20of%20repute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20geez%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20associate%20professor%20of%20government%20and%20politics%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20really%20seems%20like%20a%20radical%20departure%20even%20for%20the%20defense%20think%20tank%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%2020%20years%20of%20researching%20nuclear%20arms%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20post%20at%20RAND%20and%20advising%20the%20US%20Defense%20Secretary's%20office%20%E2%80%94%20he'd%20never%20seen%20such%20overt%20posturing%20about%20nukes%20against%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper's%20author%2C%20Greg%20Weaver%2C%20is%20influential%20and%20experienced.%20A%20former%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%2C%20Weaver%20was%20also%20principal%20director%20for%20US%20nuclear%20and%20missile%20defense%20policy%20at%20the%20Defense%20Department%20during%20the%20Obama%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20nuclear%20target%2C%20his%20paper%20wrote%2C%20might%20be%20Chinese%20ground%20troops%20sailing%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20later%2C%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20published%20a%20separate%2C%20similar%20paper%20by%20political%20scientist%20Matthew%20Kroenig.%20He%20was%20one%20of%2012%20experts%20appointed%20by%20Congress%20to%20advise%20US%20nuclear%20strategy.%20His%20report's%20title%20began%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fin-depth-research-reports%2Freport%2Fdeliberate-nuclear-use-in-a-war-over-taiwan-scenarios-and-considerations-for-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BDeliberate%20nuclear%20use%20in%20a%20war%20over%20Taiwan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20author%20outright%20argued%20for%20a%20first-strike%20nuclear%20attack%20on%20China.%20But%20they%20asked%20the%20US%20to%20seriously%20consider%20the%20option%20for%20a%20Taiwan%20war%2C%20largely%20as%20a%20deterrent%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20let%20Beijing%20know%20it's%20on%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlarmed%2C%20several%20US%20nuclear%20scholars%20rushed%20to%20criticize%20the%20papers%2C%20including%20Kearn%2C%20who%20slammed%20them%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2024%2F03%2Fstrategic-myopia-the-proposed-first-use-of-tactical-nuclear-weapons-to-defend-taiwan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bstrategic%20myopia%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20scathing%20commentary.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20later%2C%20the%20November%20reports%20still%20rest%20uneasily%20with%20top%20academics%2C%20who%20see%20the%20papers%20as%20inflammatory%20fringe%20rhetoric%20that's%20leaping%20to%20the%20fore%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver's%20arguments%20have%20been%20met%20with%20approval%20from%20other%20respected%20figures%20in%20nuclear%20scholarship%2C%20who%20say%20the%20outrage%20is%20unwarranted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20debate%20underscores%20a%20deeper%20shift%20among%20leading%20US%20minds%20toward%20a%20starkly%20more%20aggressive%20nuclear%20posture%20against%20China%2C%20which%20the%20US%20says%20will%20become%20a%20rival%20nuclear%20superpower%20by%202035%20but%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20part%20in%20crucial%20talks%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20nine%20nuclear%20arms%20scholars%20and%20US-China%20relations%20experts%20about%20the%20November%20reports%20and%20their%20implications%20on%20two%20countries%20so%20entangled%20in%20their%20economies%20and%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20that%20China%20is%20becoming%20conventionally%20powerful%2C%20the%20US%20threats%20of%20nuclear%20first-use%20are%20moving%20further%20to%20the%20forefront%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20James%20Acton%2C%20co-director%20of%20the%20Nuclear%20Policy%20Program%20at%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20for%20International%20Peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20sense%20is%20that%20what%20Greg%20and%20Matt%20were%20writing%20is%20very%20much%20a%20reflection%20of%20what%20already%20goes%20on%20within%20the%20US%20military%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220183b21a-ec25-4a8e-b215-4524af6e1e37%5C%22%3E'The%20Chinese%20read%20everything%20we%20write%20about%20them'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20US%20nuclear%20policy%20doesn't%20rule%20out%20first%20strikes.%20But%20scholars%20who%20disagree%20with%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver%2C%20several%20of%20whom%20work%20closely%20with%20experts%20in%20China%2C%20warned%20against%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20a%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20dangerous%20line%20of%20thinking%2C%20and%20it's%20extremely%20reckless%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lyle%20Goldstein%2C%20director%20of%20the%20China%20Initiative%20at%20Brown%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20such%20threats%20would%20only%20escalate%20tensions%2C%20not%20shock%20China%20into%20backing%20off%20from%20Taiwan%20as%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver%20might%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20known%20for%20decades%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20may%20launch%20a%20nuclear%20first%20strike%2C%20said%20Goldstein.%20The%20US%20once%20floated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffas.org%2Fpublication%2Fnukes-in-the-taiwan-crisis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enuclear%20retaliation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201958%20if%20China%20invaded%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20stationed%20nuclear%20weapons%20on%20the%20island%20until%201974.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Goldstein%20visited%20China%20in%20early%202023%2C%20local%20experts%20reiterated%20to%20him%20that%20the%20country%20sees%20Washington%20as%20growing%20extremely%20aggressive%2C%20and%20still%20actively%20discusses%20how%20the%20US%20may%20launch%20a%20nuclear%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20Kroenig%20is%20right.%20Maybe%20China%20will%20say%3A%20'OK%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20nuclear%20war%2C%20forget%20this%20whole%20thing%2C%20we're%20not%20interested%20in%20Taiwan%20at%20all.'%20But%20I%20don't%20think%20so%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20the%20opposite%20will%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActon%20of%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20for%20International%20Peace%20also%20disagreed%20that%20the%20US%20should%20emphasize%20its%20strike%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20already%20thinks%20this.%20Chinese%20experts%20write%20a%20lot%20about%20how%20they%20think%20the%20US%20sees%20the%20nuclear%20threshold%20as%20being%20very%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrancesca%20Giovannini%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Project%20on%20Managing%20the%20Atom%20at%20Harvard%20University's%20Kennedy%20School%2C%20fears%20all%20sides%20are%20losing%20clarity%20on%20the%20mutual%20boundaries%20that%20prevent%20a%20large-scale%20nuclear%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20China%2C%20it%20is%20obvious%20in%20their%20minds%20that%20the%20US%20now%20treats%20Taiwan%20as%20it%20would%20treat%20South%20Korea%20or%20Japan%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20we%20talk%20about%20using%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%2C%20we%20are%20very%20clearly%20blurring%20the%20commitments%20we%20have%20made.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaiwan%20is%20not%20a%20formal%20US%20ally%2C%20and%20Giovannini%20says%20American%20thought%20leaders%20are%20conflating%20a%20loss%20of%20primacy%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20with%20an%20existential%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20sure%20that%20China%20is%20watching%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver's%20rhetoric%2C%20even%20if%20their%20reports%20may%20not%20represent%20US%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20read%20everything%20that%20we%20write%20about%20them.%20Everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20foreign%20affairs%20ministry%20and%20embassy%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4f73151-0991-4549-aa1e-9fc23f52b2dc%5C%22%3EThe%20case%20for%20nukes%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKroenig%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20was%20commissioned%20last%20year%20by%20Congress%20to%20advise%20the%20US%20on%20nuclear%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20that%20if%20Taiwan%20falls%2C%20so%20too%20will%20America's%20credibility%20as%20a%20leading%20power.%20That%20makes%20Taiwan%20a%20core%20US%20interest%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20one%20the%20US%20should%20consider%20protecting%20with%20nuclear%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20are%20now%20growing%20that%20China%20is%20catching%20up%20in%20conventional%20arms%2C%20with%20missiles%20that%20can%20kill%20aircraft%20carriers%20and%20long-range%20strikes%20threatening%20Guam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20observers%20speculate%20that%20if%20Beijing%20thinks%20the%20gap%20has%20truly%20closed%2C%20it%20may%20be%20willing%20to%20invade%20on%20the%20gamble%20that%20the%20US%20won't%20risk%20conflict.%20After%20all%2C%20should%20the%20US%20go%20to%20war%20and%20fail%20to%20win%20handily%2C%20global%20faith%20in%20Washington%20would%20crack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20way%20deterrence%20could%20fail%20is%20if%20Xi%20Jinping%20thinks%3A%20'Maybe%20this%20will%20be%20easy%2C%20maybe%20I%20can%20get%20away%20with%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kroenig%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20his%20November%20report%20suggested%20that%20the%20US%20move%20past%20strategic%20ambiguity%20and%20declare%20Taiwan%20part%20of%20its%20nuclear%20umbrella.%20It%20would%20essentially%20tell%20Beijing%20that%20an%20invasion%20of%20the%20island%20risks%20nuclear%20war%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20back%20up%20that%20threat%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20US%20must%20show%20that%20it%20has%20the%20capability%20to%20nuke%20targets%20like%20navy%20ships%2C%20military%20installations%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20and%20even%20on%20the%20Chinese%20mainland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20the%20benefit%20of%20reassuring%20Xi%20that%20our%20nuclear%20weapons%20are%20not%20relevant%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeaver's%20report%20works%20off%20a%20forecast%20for%202027%2C%20when%20China%20is%20expected%20to%20possess%20700%20nuclear%20warheads.%20He%2C%20too%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20deterrence%20is%20the%20main%20goal%2C%20and%20said%20his%20paper%20doesn't%20call%20for%20the%20US%20to%20rely%20on%20tactical%20nuclear%20strikes%20for%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20open%20conflict%20does%20break%20out%2C%20they%20could%20be%20useful%20as%20a%20warfighting%20tool%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20amphibious%20landing%20force%20would%20be%20a%20stationary%20target%20for%20hours%20if%20not%20days%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20off%20the%20coast%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20relatively%20low-yield%20nuclear%20weapons%20could%20destroy%20that%20amphibious%20force%20and%20do%20little%20to%20no%20collateral%20damage%20onshore%20in%20Taiwan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20heavyweight%20in%20nuclear%20policy%2C%20he%20said%20his%20intention%20was%20to%20advocate%20for%20more%20strategic%20options%20for%20the%20US%20president.%20There%20is%20concern%20that%20if%20the%20US%20is%20stretched%20across%20two%20theaters%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20one%20with%20Russia%20and%20one%20with%20China%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20need%20solutions%20like%20nukes%20to%20deter%20or%20fight%20one%20of%20those%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20preferred%20course%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20option%20that%20the%20Chinese%20need%20to%20understand%20is%20there%2C%20and%20they%20need%20to%20take%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver's%20reports%2C%20but%20said%20the%20US%20maintains%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20high%20bar%20for%20nuclear%20employment.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20would%20only%20consider%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20extreme%20circumstances%20to%20defend%20the%20vital%20interests%20of%20the%20United%20States%20or%20its%20Allies%20and%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e5484f1-9b8a-4a95-a086-4c7e2fbd929d%5C%22%3E'It's%20important%20the%20Chinese%20understand%20this'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarshall%20Billingslea%2C%20the%20former%20US%20special%20presidential%20envoy%20for%20arms%20control%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20didn't%20see%20why%20the%20reports%20caused%20such%20a%20stir.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20already%20keep%20track%20of%20and%20plan%20for%20and%20are%20able%20to%20strike%20targets%20in%20China%20if%20that%20should%20become%20necessary.%20It's%20important%20that%20the%20Chinese%20understand%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Billingslea%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ftrumps-new-arms-control-envoy-has-a-short-clock-for-an-uphill-deal-11587913200%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eled%20US%20negotiations%20with%20Russia%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20New%20START%20Treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20is%20China's%20actions%20that%20should%20be%20cause%20for%20worry%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20intelligence%20has%20charted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-now-fastest-growing-nuclear-arsenal-in-the-world-report-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esudden%20burst%20in%20nuclear%20build-up%20from%20Bejing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20bolstered%20its%20arsenal%20to%20500%20warheads%20in%202023%2C%20up%20from%20400%20in%202022.%20China%20denies%20any%20expansion%2C%20and%20concerns%20abound%20in%20the%20US%20that%20it%20may%20soon%20become%20a%20rogue%20nuclear%20superpower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%20atomic%20era%2C%20we%20have%20not%20had%20a%20three-way%20nuclear%20arms%20race%2C%20but%20that%20is%20precisely%20what%20China%20is%20creating%2C%20that%20unpredictable%2C%20unstable%20dynamic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Billingslea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebeccah%20Heinrichs%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Hudson%20Institute's%20Keystone%20Defense%20Initiative%2C%20agreed%20with%20Kroenig%20and%20Weaver's%20core%20thesis%2C%20also%20describing%20a%20Taiwan%20invasion%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bclear%20threat%20to%20US%20vital%20interests.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20foolish%20not%20to%20give%20the%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20his%20military%20forces%20the%20most%20effective%20means%20to%20convince%20the%20PRC%20it%20will%20not%20take%20Taiwan%20at%20an%20acceptable%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Weaver%20was%20asked%20if%20more%20aggressive%20rhetoric%20from%20the%20US%20could%20be%20used%20by%20China%20to%20justify%20its%20nuclear%20build-up%2C%20he%20said%20Beijing's%20expansion%20is%20happening%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20already%20doing%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20doing%20that%20long%20before%20Matt%20and%20I%20wrote%20our%20analyses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2265c3f298-738c-440e-8eed-536934e79de8%5C%22%3ESome%20experts%20fear%20a%20wider%20fallout%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Jake%20Werner%2C%20acting%20director%20of%20the%20East%20Asia%20Program%20at%20the%20Quincy%20Institute%20for%20Responsible%20Statescraft%2C%20raised%20concern%20that%20the%20November%20reports%20would%20empower%20anti-US%20parties%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20American%20public%20doesn't%20understand%20that%20there%20are%20different%20positions%20in%20the%20Chinese%20debate.%20There%20are%20people%20who%20are%20very%20aggressive%2C%20there%20are%20people%20who%20are%20very%20cautious%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20threat%20perceptions%20are%20so%20elevated%20on%20the%20Chinese%20side%2C%20saying%20things%20like%20this%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20used%20in%20a%20way%20that%20exacerbates%20fear%20in%20the%20Chinese%20public%2C%20if%20not%20among%20officials%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKearn%20of%20St.%20Johns%20University%20said%20the%20US%20has%20more%20than%20China%20to%20worry%20about%20if%20it%20makes%20the%20threat%3B%20it%20could%20lose%20credibility%20with%20allies%20like%20South%20Korea%20or%20Japan%20if%20they%20believe%20Washington%20is%20bluffing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20what%20foundation%20of%20diplomatic%20or%20political%20relations%20can%20you%20even%20pretend%20to%20have%20credibility%20in%20that%20situation%2C%20of%20threatening%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%201945%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20threatening%20war%20%E2%80%94%20much%20less%20nuclear%20war%20%E2%80%94%20over%20Taiwan%20would%20be%20deeply%20unpopular%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20where%20the%20Amer