20is%20built%20with%20cob%2C%20which%20is%20a%20mixture%20of%20sand%2C%20clay%2C%20straw%2C%20soil%20and%20water%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKnock%20on%20sustainability%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20passed%20by%20Dhunar%20Gaon%20in%20Rishikesh%20in%202021%2C%20was%20met%20with%20an%20unusual%20sight.%20Albanian%20folk%20songs%20reverberated%20through%20the%20air%2C%20interrupted%20only%20by%20the%20beats%20of%20Japanese%20rock%20music%2C%20German%20techno%2C%20and%20Daler%20Mehndi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ETunak%20Tunak%20Tun%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20grooving%20to%20these%20lively%20tempos%20were%20a%20group%20of%2090%20individuals.%20A%20closer%20look%20at%20them%20would%20reveal%20their%20vivid%20origins%20%E2%80%94%20Brazil%2C%20Australia%2C%20Germany%2C%20France%2C%20Canada%2C%20Slovenia%20%E2%80%94%2018%20nationalities%2C%20to%20be%20precise%2C%20Ansh%20states.%20Their%20rhythms%20though%20unchoreographed%2C%20would%20seem%20almost%20synced%20to%20an%20onlooker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20don%E2%80%99t%20be%20distracted%20by%20their%20moves%2C%20Ansh%20urges%2C%20look%20under%20their%20feet%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FOtYaplok1Z8%3Fsi%3DtIHOIpE9o8aOTj38%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20the%20material%20the%20group%20spent%20months%20dancing%20upon%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CCob%20is%20a%20mixture%20of%20clay%2C%20sand%2C%20soil%2C%20straw%20and%20water.%20We%20chopped%20wheat%20and%20rice%20straw%2C%20put%20it%20on%20a%20tarp%2C%20and%20then%20invited%20the%20group%20to%20dance%20on%20it%20until%20it%20formed%20a%20burrito-shaped%20dough.%20Once%20stable%2C%20the%20dough%20does%20not%20break%20and%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20building%20material.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20they%20brought%20in%20foreign%20hands%20for%20the%20project%2C%20Raghav%20laughs%20and%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20planned.%20We%20put%20out%20a%20request%20on%20the%20website%20%E2%80%98Workaway%E2%80%99%2C%20asking%20people%20interested%20in%20sustainable%20building%20to%20join%20us.%20Through%20the%20months%2C%20we%20got%20many%20who%20were%20keen%20on%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20these%20were%20people%20who%20did%20not%20specially%20make%20a%20trip%20to%20dance%20on%20the%20cob.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20already%20heading%20to%20Rishikesh%20for%20a%20vacation.%20But%20their%20interest%20in%20natural%20building%20attracted%20them%20to%20our%20site.%20We%20set%20up%20a%20dorm%20for%20them%20in%20the%20village%20Umrisen%2C%20where%20we%20were%20camping%20out%20during%20the%20construction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAishwarya%20Lakhani%2C%20an%20interior%20designer%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20was%20a%20part%20of%20this%20community%20effort%2C%20says%20she%20had%20always%20been%20meaning%20to%20get%20into%20conscious%20design.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20came%20across%20this%20project%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20opportunity.%20I%20had%20been%20wanting%20to%20go%20to%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20for%20months%20and%20since%20it%20was%20coinciding%20with%20my%20Rishikesh%20travel%20dates%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20head%20there.%20Right%20from%20day%20one%2C%20it%20was%20a%20warm%20experience%20staying%20with%20the%20villagers.%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20took%20good%20care%20of%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20echoes%20the%20thoughts%20of%20the%20others%20when%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20in%20awe%20that%20such%20a%20thing%20could%20be%20achieved%20in%20a%20remote%20location.%20Having%20practised%20with%20reusable%20materials%20and%20natural%20plasters%20myself%2C%20it%20%5Bthis%20project%5D%20gave%20me%20hope%20and%20inspiration%20knowing%20that%20the%20sky%20is%20the%20limit%20when%20using%20cob%20for%20built%20environments.%20Working%20with%20cob%20grounds%20you.%20Dancing%20on%20the%20mud%20is%20an%20emotion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBharat%20Rolaniya%2C%20an%20architect%2C%20seconds%20Lakhani.%20%E2%80%9CWorking%20with%20mud%2C%20specifically%20cob%20was%20very%20intuitive%20to%20me.%20Being%20a%20natural%20building%20construction%20practitioner%2C%20I%20enjoyed%20working%20with%20cob.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20like%20finding%20yourself.%20In%20architecture%2C%20one%20tends%20to%20feel%20like%20they%20are%20transforming%20a%20building%2C%20but%20working%20with%20mud%20and%20cob%20shows%20you%20that%20it%20goes%20both%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20they%20transform%20you%20in%20turn%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20the%20brother%20duo%20three%20years%20to%20build%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort.%20They%20recall%20the%20journey%20as%20revelationary%20in%20many%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20two%20city%20kids%20who%20did%20not%20know%20much%2C%20we%20learnt%20a%20lot%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ansh.%20%E2%80%9CTravelling%20from%20the%20last%20motorable%20point%20in%20Phoolchatti%20to%20the%20Umrisen%20village%20involved%20crossing%20a%20wooden%20bridge%20across%20a%20tributary%20Heval%20and%20then%20hiking%20for%201.5%20km.%20Each%20time%20we%20had%20to%20get%20groceries%2C%20we%20had%20to%20make%20a%2020%20km%20trek.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20effort%20was%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20comprises%20a%20loft%20bed%2C%20a%20cave%20bedroom%2C%20a%20kitchenette%2C%20and%20a%20bathroom%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.theb