-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358226%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20concept%20of%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20to%20showcase%20the%20properties%20of%20sustainable%20and%20natural%20building%20materials%20such%20as%20cob%20in%20modern-day%20structures%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20a%20masterpiece.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20a%20work%20of%20many%20hands%2C%E2%80%9D%20points%20out%20Raghav.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20spend%20almost%20six%20to%20eight%20hours%20building%20the%20home%20and%20never%20took%20a%20day%20off.%20Whether%20it%20was%20hot%20sun%20with%20temperatures%20crossing%2044%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20raining%2C%20or%20even%20dark%20and%20cold%20in%20winter%20%E2%80%94%20nothing%20stopped%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20add%20to%20it%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20easy%20being%20outsiders%20in%20a%20village.%20But%20instead%20of%20resisting%20guidance%2C%20Raghav%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20let%20the%20villagers%20take%20over.%E2%80%9D%20And%20as%20the%20brothers%20soon%20realised%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20wisdom%20to%20be%20gleaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20let%20them%20teach%20us%20farming%2C%20how%20to%20use%20tools%20for%20construction%2C%20how%20to%20pick%20up%20rocks%2C%20break%20them%2C%20and%20then%20build%20a%20frugal%20trolley%20to%20transport%20these%20rocks%2C%20bamboo%20and%20wooden%20logs%20back%20and%20forth.%20We%20learnt%20how%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Erotis%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20flatbread)%20using%20a%20%3Cem%3Echula%20%3C%2Fem%3E(earthen%20stove)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%202024%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20was%20ready%20to%20host%20its%20first%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20planning%20to%20make%20a%20trip%20here%2C%20full%20disclosure%3A%20reaching%20the%20homestay%20from%20Heval%20involves%20a%2030-minute%20trek%2C%20with%20some%20pockets%20posing%20a%20steep%20climb.%20But%20the%20beauty%20compensates%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20set%20foot%20into%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%2C%20%3Cem%3Edeja%20vu%3C%2Fem%3E%20will%20creep%20up%20on%20you%2C%20making%20all%20those%20fairy%20tales%20seem%20believable%20at%20long%20last.%20In%20every%20sense%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20impersonates%20a%20goblin%E2%80%99s%20den%2C%20and%20you%20might%20almost%20expect%20to%20see%20one%20hanging%20around%20during%20your%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20homestay%20is%20cradled%20by%20a%20mountain%20forest%20and%20perched%20high%20on%20a%20ridge%20such%20that%20it%20overlooks%20an%20expanse%20of%20emerald%20%E2%80%94%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20river%20Ganges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20coolness%20engulfs%20the%20home%20in%20the%20summers%2C%20while%20an%20ambient%20temperature%20is%20maintained%20during%20the%20winters%20%E2%80%94%20gratis%20the%2019-inch%20thick%20mud%20walls.%20As%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20iterate%2C%20the%20home%20was%20designed%20with%20an%20open%20plan%20in%20mind%20with%20a%20cosy%20loft%20bed%20and%20a%20cave-like%20bedroom%20(which%20accommodates%20two%20people%20each)%2C%20a%20kitchenette%20with%20pots%20and%20pans%2C%20an%20outdoor%20barbeque%2C%20a%20woodfire%20pizza%20oven%20%E2%80%94%20made%20completely%20from%20mud%20%E2%80%94%20a%20rooftop%20garden%2C%20and%20a%20sensory%20bathroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20fairytale%20homes%20and%20was%20built%20by%20architect%20brother%20duo%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20Kumar%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20fairytale%20homes%20and%20was%20built%20by%20architect%20brother%20duo%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20Kumar%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details.%20From%20a%20table%20made%20using%20discarded%20slate%20from%20an%20old%20home%E2%80%99s%20roof%20and%20a%20chandelier%20crafted%20from%20driftwood%20from%20the%20river%20Ganges%2C%20each%20piece%20of%20decor%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F285477%2Fsustainable-homes-energy-efficient-zero-waste-cut-electricity-water-bills-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20sustainable%20rendition%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20served%20is%20unique%20too%20%E2%80%94%20a%20simple%20meal%20of%20%3Cem%3Ealoo%20sabzi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(potato%20vegetable)%2C%20%3Cem%3Eroti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Edal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20dish%20made%20of%20lentils).%20When%20you%20aren%E2%80%99t%20feasting%20(your%20mouth)%20on%20the%20home-made%20fiestas%20and%20(your%20eyes)%20on%20the%20view%2C%20you%20can%20take%20part%20in%20a%20rafting%20session%20on%20the%20river%20Ganges%3B%20or%20go%20bird%20watching%20to%20spot%20the%20White-crested%20Himalayan%20Forest%20Laughing%20Thrush%20or%20the%20Red-billed%20Blue%20Magpie%3B%20or%20learn%20to%20brew%20%3Cem%3Ekombucha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20fizzy%20fermented%20drink)%3B%20or%20go%20foraging%20for%20mushrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomedays%2C%20the%20weather%20might%20play%20spoilsport%2C%20but%20dark%20skies%20are%20no%20deterrent%20to%20the%20mood%20at%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort.%20Candlelit%20dinners%20and%20torches%20come%20to%20the%20rescue.%20Applaud%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20for%20this%20work%20of%20art%20and%20they%20say%20it%20is%20the%20material%20%E2%80%98cob%E2%80%99%20that%20is%20the%20real%20hero.%20When%20pitted%20against%20other%20sustainable%20materials%2C%20cob%20emerges%20a%20winner%20for%20its%20durability%20and%20beauty%2C%20all%20tied%20into%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20is%20where%20these%20ideas%20are%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20space%20where%20artistry%20meets%20sustainability%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20circular%20design%2C%20research%2C%20build%2C%20and%20innovation%20studio%20in%20the%20woods%20in%20Rishikesh%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20is%20attempting%20to%20reinstill%20people%E2%80%99s%20beliefs%20in%20materials%20that%20were%20used%20centuries%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEspecially%20materials%20whose%20desirability%20has%20gone%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ansh%20adds.%20With%20a%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F354933%2Fombak-sustainable-furniture-shruthi-prakash-rattan-chairs-table-wall-decor-from-banana-fibres-in-indonesia-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiobased%20materials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20mycelium%20(a%20root-like%20structure%20of%20a%20fungus)%2C%20seaweed%20bioplastic%20and%20mud%2C%20the%20studio%20is%20an%20ode%20to%20how%20the%20best%20architecture%20is%20born%20out%20of%20the%20simplest%20ideas.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wanted%20to%20showcase%20that%20in%20a%20world%20where%20everything%20is%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20fast%20food%2C%20fast%20deliveries%2C%20speed%20dating%20%E2%80%94%20we%20can%20build%20something%20slow%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raghav%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20take%20mud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20decor%20is%20the%20homestay%20is%20made%20out%20of%20recycled%20wood%2C%20old%20doors%20and%20cob%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358231%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20decor%20in%20the%20homestay%20is%20made%20out%20of%20recycled%20wood%2C%20old%20doors%20and%20cob%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20dismissed%20as%20%3Cem%3Ekaccha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(raw)%2C%20mud%20homes%20are%20now%20starting%20to%20see%20an%20upswing%20in%20architecture.%20%E2%80%9CMud%20was%20known%20as%20a%20material%20that%20could%20survive%20the%20test%20of%20time.%20But%20then%20cases%20began%20emerging%20where%20the%20foundation%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20strong%20and%20water%20began%20entering%20the%20structure.%20Slowly%2C%20the%20material%20lost%20popularity%20and%20cement%20came%20in.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaghav%20does%20not%20have%20a%20bone%20to%20pick%20with%20the%20material%20in%20itself%2C%20but%20rather%20with%20how%20it%20has%20become%20a%20status%20symbol.%20%E2%80%9CCement%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20Indian%20labourers%20%E2%80%94%20pointing%20to%20how%20its%20use%20should%20be%20moderated%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raghav%20notes.%20%E2%80%9CAn%20overuse%20can%20be%20toxic.%20It%20makes%20the%20structure%20non-breathable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%2C%20the%20brothers%20decided%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F284927%2Fkerala-eco-friendly-sustainable-mud-house-stays-cool-cost-efficient-construction%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecob%20as%20the%20material%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20vetting%20its%20feasibility%2C%20they%20relied%20on%20an%20old%20English%20saying%3A%20A%20cob%20house%20which%20has%20a%20good%20boot%20(good%20foundation)%20and%20good%20hat%20(roof%20with%20large%20overhangs)%20will%20survive%20a%20hundred%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FfXNSUfyfnrY%3Fsi%3DzTeYiwb87_8-vqEQ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20the%20strategic%20location%20of%20the%20homestay%20proves%20a%20boon.%20%E2%80%9CTiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20perched%20on%20a%20hill%20and%20gets%20good%20sunlight.%20In%20cases%20of%20heavy%20rainfall%2C%20the%20water%20runs%20down%20the%20valley%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raghav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20its%20exterior%2C%20but%20even%20the%20interiors%20in%20the%20home%20are%20reflective%20of%20sustainable%20design.%20For%20this%2C%20the%20brothers%20credit%20the%20group%20that%20chipped%20in%20to%20help%20them%20build%20the%20homestay.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20weren%E2%80%99t%20artists%2C%20but%20cob%20is%20such%20a%20forgiving%20material%20to%20work%20with%20that%20the%20process%20almost%20becomes%20intuitive%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Ansh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%20their%20creations%20and%20sculptures%20%E2%80%94%20elephants%2C%20mushrooms%2C%20coral%20life%20%E2%80%94%20live%20on%20the%20shelves%20of%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort.%20Ansh%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20see%20this%20house%20as%20a%20museum%20where%20we%20exhibit%20products%20and%20materials%20of%20different%20designers%20working%20with%20waste%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F312922%2Fdelhi-engineer-innovates-biodegradable-thermocol-from-crop-stubble%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiodegradable%20biomaterials%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%20You%20can%20take%20a%20look%20when%20you%20are%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20beauty%20in%20each%20nook%20and%20crevice%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20a%20breathing%20fairytale.%20Knock%20once.%20Who%20knows%2C%20Goldilocks%20might%20open%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722236762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-1721812338.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D358205%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20Kumar%2C%20architects%20from%20Delhi%2C%20created%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%2C%20a%20homestay%20in%20Rishikesh.%20Made%20using%20cob%2C%20this%20sustainable%20retreat%20aims%20to%20reconnect%20people%20